# World & Vehicles Local Runtime Context

You are working in a local world or vehicle runtime/test hotspot.

Start from touched code/tests in these roots first. Do NOT auto-load `docs/design/core-architecture.md` for local travel, persistent-player-root, or world-runtime cleanup.

Read `docs/design/README.md` only to decide whether a domain doc is needed. Load docs only as needed:

1. `docs/design/world-and-vehicles.md` and `docs/design/world-and-scenes.md` when local world semantics are unclear
2. `docs/design/world-scene-contracts.md` only when the touched seam changes scene wiring, travel contracts, or scene-level validation behavior
3. `docs/design/extensible-development-contracts.md` only for scene/checkpoint/interactable/NPC/save integration changes
4. `docs/design/core-architecture.md` only if the change crosses events, save, persistence, or another domain, or if local intent is unclear
5. `.agent/skills/refactoring-and-test-hygiene/SKILL.md` for local runtime refactor/test cleanup

If the task becomes scene, terrain, prefab, editor-state, or broader world-integration work, switch to `.cursor/rules/world-vehicles-context.mdc`.
